    "output": "## Done: Agent container running as non-root\n\n### Files created\n- **Dockerfile.agent** — Node 20 slim + git + curl + jq + Claude Code (`@anthropic-ai/claude-code`), runs as non-root `agent` user (UID 1000). `--dangerously-skip-permissions` confirmed working.\n- **agent/watch.sh** — SSE-driven watcher script that connects to `/api/events`, picks up pending tasks, and runs `claude -p \"/agent <id>\" --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n- **.env** — Contains `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN` (gitignored)\n\n### Files modified\n- **docker-compose.yml** — Added `agent` service on orbiter network, mounts workspace + persistent claude-home volume, passes OAuth token from .env\n- **.gitignore** — Added `.env`\n\n### Also fixed\n- Disabled `orchestrator-api.service` systemd unit that was binding port 3001 and conflicting with the Docker prod container\n\n### How to verify\n1. `docker compose ps` — agent container is running\n2. `docker compose logs agent` — shows connected to SSE stream\n3. `docker compose exec agent bash -c 'whoami && claude --version'` — runs as non-root, Claude Code available\n4. Create a pending task → agent auto-picks it up and runs Claude\n\n### Architecture\n```\nhost:3001 → prod container (Hono API + static)\nagent container → http://prod:3001 (Docker DNS)\nagent runs as UID 1000 (non-root) → --dangerously-skip-permissions works\nOAuth token passed via .env → CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN env var\n```"
